      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "If you absolutely cannot see a doctor today, here's what you can do at home to minimize the risk of worsening:\n\n1. Keep the area clean: Gently wash the wound with mild soap and water. Pat it dry with a clean towel.\n2. Apply antibiotic ointment: Use a generous amount of antibiotic ointment to cover the wound completely. This will help prevent infection.\n3. Heat soak: Soak a clean cloth in warm (not hot) water, wring it out, and place it over the wound for 20 minutes. This will help with pain and swelling.\n4. Cover it up: After soaking, apply a thick layer of antibiotic ointment over the wound, then cover it with a sterile dressing or gauze bandage.\n5. Monitor closely: Keep an eye on the wound for any signs of increased redness, swelling, warmth, or discharge that may indicate an infection.\n6. Take it easy: Avoid any activities that could stress the wound.\n\nRemember, this is a temporary measure. If you notice any signs of infection, seek medical attention immediately. This advice is not a substitute for professional medical care.",
